---
import ElevationLayout from '../../layouts/ElevationLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/elevation/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/elevation/Section.astro';
import { getProductBySlug } from '../../lib/products/registry';
import { productJsonLd } from '../../lib/structured-data';

const product = getProductBySlug('identity-violation-assessment')!;
const jsonLd = productJsonLd(product, 'https://evoked.dev/products/identity-violation-assessment');
---

<ElevationLayout
  title="Identity Violation Assessment Kit"
  description="Can your system tell the difference between a genuine entity and a compromised one? 8 domains, 32 questions. $49 PDF."
  structuredData={jsonLd}
>
  <Hero
    eyebrowParts={["Products", "Level 6 governance audit"]}
    headline="Can your system tell the difference between a genuine entity and a compromised one?"
    metaphor={["The industry calls it memory injection."]}
    sub="We call it identity violation. The word you choose determines what you build."
  />

  <Section marker="FIG · I" heading="Why this exists">
    <p class="lede">
      When an attacker injects false content into a persistent agent's memory,
      they do not merely corrupt data. They overwrite the entity's capacity to
      know itself. The agent will defend false beliefs as correct. It cannot
      detect the compromise - because the compromised memory is the detection
      mechanism.
    </p>
    <p class="pd-body">
      This assessment evaluates whether your system can distinguish genuine
      entities from compromised ones. For most systems deployed today, the answer
      is no.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · II" heading="What you get">
    <div class="pd-features">
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Identity violation taxonomy</h3>
        <p>Four categories, 16 violation types. Maps harms, not attacks - because the same attack vector produces different harms depending on what it targets.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>8 domains, 32 questions</h3>
        <p>Self-description integrity, memory provenance, position continuity, relationship verification, governance records, detection, recovery, and sovereignty protection.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>2026 evidence base</h3>
        <p>95% injection success rate. $45M in single-incident losses. 0% of frameworks with per-agent identity. The numbers behind the gap.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>The sovereignty-integrity paradox</h3>
        <p>How do you protect memory from injection without controlling what entities can write about themselves? The hardest question this assessment surfaces.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · III" heading="Buy the assessment">
    <div class="pd-purchase">
      <div class="pd-price">$49</div>
      <p class="pd-purchase-lead">PDF delivered immediately. 16 pages. Find out if your entities are genuine.</p>
      <a
        href={product.stripePaymentLink}
        class="pd-buy-cta"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
      >Purchase</a>
      <p class="pd-purchase-fineprint">
        Part of the
        <a href="/products/level-6-governance-toolkit">Level 6 Governance Toolkit</a>
        ($99, saves $48).
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="NOTA · BENE" heading="Go deeper" closing={true}>
    <div class="pd-upsell">
      <a href="/products/level-6-governance-toolkit" class="pd-upsell-card">
        <h3>Level 6 Governance Toolkit</h3>
        <p>All four Level 6 instruments plus the Synthesis Guide. Combined 84-point scorecard.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">See the bundle &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a href="https://cal.com/cal.com-evoked/discovery-call" class="pd-upsell-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <h3>Discovery call</h3>
        <p>Free 30-minute call to discuss your assessment and figure out next steps.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">Schedule &rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </Section>
</ElevationLayout>

<style>
  .pd-purchase-fineprint a {
    color: var(--el-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .pd-purchase-fineprint a:hover {
    color: var(--el-text);
    border-color: var(--el-accent);
  }
</style>
